In this article, President Joe Biden proclaims June 2023 as National Ocean Month and emphasizes the importance of protecting and conserving the ocean. He highlights how the ocean sustains livelihoods, connects economies, and provides recreation and rejuvenation. The article mentions that the climate crisis is impacting marine life, coastal communities, and the ocean economy, with rising temperatures forcing marine life to move and threatening food supplies. The administration has implemented the United States Ocean Climate Action Plan, which aims to advance offshore wind projects, modernize infrastructure, and support communities affected by pollution. They are also cracking down on illegal fishing and working to strengthen sustainable fisheries. Additionally, the administration is taking steps to designate new national marine sanctuaries and invest in nature-based climate solutions. The article concludes by emphasizing the need to protect and conserve the ocean for future generations.